{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","title":"setUser:emails:","modules":[{"name":"PushwooshCore"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"setUser:emails:","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)PWConfiguration(cm)setUser:emails:","fragments":[{"text":"+ ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setUser:emails:"}],"roleHeading":"Type Method","role":"symbol"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/pushwooshcore\/pwconfiguration\/setuser:emails:"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PWConfiguration\/setUser:emails:","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"+ (","kind":"text"},{"text":"void","preciseIdentifier":"c:v","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setUser:"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSString","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSString"},{"text":" *) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"userId"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"emails:","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSArray","text":"NSArray","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" *) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"emails"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"userId","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The custom user identifier."}]}]},{"name":"emails","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Array of email address strings to associate with the user.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Convenience method that combines ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setUserId:"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"setEmails:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into a single","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"server request. This is more efficient than calling both methods separately","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and ensures atomic association of user ID with emails."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this during login or registration flows when you have both user ID"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and email available simultaneously.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Example","anchor":"Example","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Complete registration with user ID and emails:"}]},{"code":["class RegistrationManager {","","    func completeRegistration(_ registration: RegistrationData) {","        \/\/ Create user on backend","        APIClient.shared.createUser(registration) { result in","            guard case .success(let user) = result else { return }","","            \/\/ Set both user ID and emails in single operation","            var emails = [user.email]","            if let secondaryEmail = registration.secondaryEmail {","                emails.append(secondaryEmail)","            }","","            Pushwoosh.configure.setUser(user.id, emails: emails)","","            \/\/ Set initial user tags","            Pushwoosh.configure.setTags([","                \"registration_date\": ISO8601DateFormatter().string(from: Date()),","                \"registration_source\": registration.source.rawValue,","                \"account_type\": user.accountType.rawValue,","                \"has_completed_onboarding\": false","            ])","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["   when you need confirmation."],"syntax":null}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore","doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PWConfiguration"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Sets user identifier and emails together in a single operation.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore/documentation/PushwooshCore/PWConfiguration":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"PWConfiguration","fragments":[{"text":"PWConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/pushwooshcore\/pwconfiguration","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PWConfiguration","kind":"symbol","abstract":[]},"doc://com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore/documentation/PushwooshCore/PWConfiguration/setUser:emails:":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"setUser:emails:","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"setUser:emails:","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets user identifier and emails together in a single operation."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PWConfiguration\/setUser:emails:","url":"\/documentation\/pushwooshcore\/pwconfiguration\/setuser:emails:","fragments":[{"text":"+ ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setUser:emails:","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore/documentation/PushwooshCore":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore","url":"\/documentation\/pushwooshcore","title":"PushwooshCore","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"Core foundation module for Pushwoosh SDK.","type":"text"}]}}}